.TH "ata_pci_sff_activate_host" 9 "ata_pci_sff_activate_host" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_pci_sff_activate_host \- start SFF host, request IRQ and register it
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ata_pci_sff_activate_host
.BI "(struct ata_host *host "  ","
.BI "irq_handler_t irq_handler "  ","
.BI "struct scsi_host_template *sht "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "host" 12
target SFF ATA host
.IP "irq_handler" 12
irq_handler used when requesting IRQ(s)
.IP "sht" 12
scsi_host_template to use when registering the host

This is the counterpart of \fBata_host_activate\fP for SFF ATA
hosts.  This separate helper is necessary because SFF hosts
use two separate interrupts in legacy mode.

LOCKING:
Inherited from calling layer (may sleep).
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno otherwise.
